reviewText: After nearly 3 years, CBS FINALLY released the final season of this show on DVD ... I bought both Vol.1 & 2 at the same time.This gritty, realistic, well scripted and cast show is one of the all-time best  to ever be broadcast on network TV !! It is no coincidence that many up & coming actors ( who later were 'A' list in Hollywood ... like Robert Redford for example) fine tuned their acting chops by appearing on this show !!I have all 4 seasons now on DVD ... and glad of it ... this is a show that can be watched more than once, and your enjoyment level does not diminish one bit !

reviewText: AT LONG LAST~ SEASON FOUR RELEASED ON DVD~ WITH NEW DIGITAL SIGHT AND SOUND.THE SNOWBALL: ROBERT REDFORD as Young hussler using bootleg LETHAL booze to advance HIS GOAL OF WORKING with Frank Nitti and the mob~ this one of the BEST of SEASON four with a great ending~ Redford looks very young and was just a bit player on the Desilu Lot.JAKE DANCE: LETHAL GINGER JAKE bootleg booze has some users blind and or DEAD~ this was a SECOND ATTEMPT AT A SPIN OFF~ BUT WAS NEVER PICKED UP BY THE NETWORKS THIS TIES IN WITH NESS AND THE UNTOUCHABLES ON FINDING THE GUILTY BOOTLEGGERS.BLUES FOR A GONE GOOSE: Jazz is the cover for bootlegs business~GLOBE OF DEATH~ EXCELLENT 5 STAR EPISODE~ HEROINE IS SMUGGLED IN A GLOBE FROM THE FAR EAST and hidden in a mofia bank~ lots of great guest stars and one of the BEST plots in the entire series~ added fun is a double cross by one of the Mob to steal the drugs right under the nose of Frank Nitti.AN EYE FOR AN EYE:~~~ everyone is out to close down Solly Girsh who becomes one of  the up and rising bootleggers for the mob.JUNK MAN: a junk yard is the cover and front for a huge booze cover~ and the fun is the double cross and under cover agent who helps close them down.THE MAN IN THE COOLER: one of my favorite~ Ness brings a con out of prison to work with him to bring down BIG AUGIE~ a 300 POUND plus man who uses his COOLER for his illegal bootleg business~ interesting characters and first rate plot. JD Cannon as the con who wants to go straight but is tempted by the fast buck.THE BUTCHER'S BOY: FUN~ a World War 1 Hero uses his former soldiers as his underlings to promote his booze profits along the way someone turns on HIM~ GREAT plot.THE SPOILER: A hood comes back to the US and everyone on both sides of the law wants to get him.ONE LAST KILLING: A dead hoods wife refuses to ID the man who killed him~ but soon Ness may be saving her life~THE GIANT KILLER: a con has days to live so he turns to Ness to find out who turned on him~ and tipped off the FEDS~THE CHARLIE ARGOS STORY: a man turns up and claims to be the long lost son of a RICH DEAD MOFIA DON FAMILY~ GOOD PLOT.THE JAZZ MAN: Ness goes under cover to the New Orleans JAZZ crowd hot on the heals of a huge drug shipment. BAD plot.THE TORPEDO: 2 RIVAL mofia dons are out to destroy each other again and Ness is out to get them both.LINE OF FIRE: the death of a dance hall girl has a man take vengence into his own hands.A TASTE FOR PINEAPPLE: someone puts out a contract for Ness ~ and he is blinded by a PINEAPPLE AKA bomb~ he has to cope with his own blindness but allow his MEN to help solve the crime. LAST OF THE SERIES GOOD STORY:what you may not know~ THE UNTOUCHABLES WAS PART OF THE DESILU PLAY HOUSE IN 1959 and was a 2 parter that ended up being a movie called the SCARFACED MOB~ AND eventually picked up as series it ran from 1959-1963~ many big parts then were filled with NOW BIG TIME ACTORS INCLUDING ROBERT REDFORD, LEONARD NIMOY, LEE MARVIN, PETER FALK CAROL O'CONNOR  AND MANY MORE. it was considered one of the MOST violent TV series of the 1960s and is mild compared to what we have now. WEll done and holds up over time due to excellent plot and character development. GLAD THEY FINALLY RELEASED THIS ENTIRE SERIES~ at long last.
summary: Last Season~ worth the wait~~~~ 5 STARS~

reviewText: I think that the final season was not as good as the first three although it is still a must have. I think we all know that Elliot Ness did not accomplish all that is portrayed in these episodes but it is still good gangster television. Robert Stack is an excellent actor in his own right and so were the others who comprised "The Untouchables". It is still good television and very much entertaining. A classic!
